WebApiClient is a simple and powerful .NET Portable Library built to work as a middle layer between your application and a RESTFul service, like the Microsoft WebApi.
It provides methods to make asynchronous, typed WebApi requests using the HttpClient class.
It takes care of all the logic to create the request, wait for the response, handle exceptions and convert the response into an object, leaving you free of writing repetitive code.
Supported Platforms: - .NET Framework 4.5 - Windows 8 Apps - Windows Phone Silverlight 8

FeedPackage.Description:
WFC behavoir to log soap messages and headers with log4net
Add the following in your wcf configuration <system.serviceModel>:
<extensions> <behaviorExtensions> <add name="log4netOutputBehavior" type="WcfBehavoirSoapLog4net.Behavoirs.Log4NetOutputBehaviorExtensionElement, WcfBehavoirSoapLog4net, Version=1.0.0.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null" /> <add name="log4netOutputBehaviorHeaders" type="WcfBehavoirSoapLog4net.Behavoirs.Log4NetOutputHeadersBehaviorExtensionElement, WcfBehavoirSoapLog4net, Version=1.0.0.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null" /> </behaviorExtensions> </extensions> <behaviors> <endpointBehaviors> <behavior name="log4NetBehavior"> <log4netOutputBehavior /> <log4netOutputBehaviorHeaders /> </behavior> </endpointBehaviors> </behaviors> ... <client> <endpoint ... behaviorConfiguration="log4NetBehavior" /> ...
